By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Lawmaker representing Kogi central senatorial district at the National Assembly, Senator Dino Melaye has berated the National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Comrade Adams Oshiomhole over his comment against the People’s Democratic Party, (PDP) at the defection rally in Uyo, Akwa Ibom State capital on Thursday. During the Defection rally for Goodswill Akpabio, Oshiomhole was quoted to have said   that the 16 years of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) was a waste. Dino while reacting to the comment on his twitter handle; listed the airport, roads, and even the stadium where he held the rally as products of the People’s Democratic Party’s 16 years rule, reminding that had Oshiomhole wasted Edo state money like that, the people of Edo would have been happier. The Kogi lawmaker who gave the attack on his twitter handle @dino_melaye said: “Oshiomole, The airport you landed at Uyo was built by PDP. The road you drove on – PDP. The stadium of the rally – PDP & you said16yrs of PDP in Akwa-Ibom state was a waste. You should have wasted Edo state money like this, the people of Edo would have been happier.’ Recall that Governor of Edo State, Godwin Obaseki bemoaned the loan burden of the state, saying it is affecting the service delivery of his government to the people of the state. National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Comrade Adams Oshiomhole was the immediate past governor Edo State. He ruled the state for 8 years and handed over to Governor Godwin Obaseki.